\section*{OPPORTUNISTIC INFECTIONS IN HIV/AIDS}

What is an opportunistic infection?
- An opportunistic infection (OI) is a disease caused by microorganism that does not normally cause illness in a person with a healthy immune system, but that may cause serious disease when the immune system is weakened.
- For example, as the immune system of people living with HIV weakens, they become susceptible to a number of opportunistic infections at different stages of HIV disease progression

